The paper deals with visual place recognition and localization, which is a common problem in robotics and autonomous vehicles. The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and Weightless Neural Networks (WNN) suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques such as CNN and WNN suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
